results.title: The Fountain of Goof FOG Tv Network A Short Story Called SQAK
results.description:
The Fountain of Goof (F.O.G.) Tv Network

Presents:  A Short Story Called: S.Q.A.K.

It was above normal temperatures along the hike and bike trail this particular spring morning -

Rather than hearing the same usual sounds of downtown traffic, nature’s wind rustling leaves among the abundance of tall trees, bird whistle calls, early morning walkers/runner’s athletic footwear rhythmically hitting the sand/gravel path -

Ducks quacking morning chow call...waiting in anticipation for mom’s strolling in with their toddlers carrying partial loaves of bread (and a smiling grandma at the helm of a rowboat...photobombs in the background) today was different.

Tho, the ducks circled along the dining area...a.k.a….a cleanup dip in the tub before breakfast...today, no one showed up to feed them.

They quietly quacked among themselves...wondering where were those cute young creatures that share the crackers/bread…?

A few minutes turned into an hour...and...as it got later...all of the ducks starting quacking loudly at the same time.

3 or 4 of the larger ducks sounded off so loudly and fierce, their calls resembled quick intervals of laughter -

It startled the young ducklings to hear such awkward and bold bursts of protests...but...at the same time, it gave them a sense of security and feelings of humor within...they began to mimic the elder’s squaking/honks.

“Quack...Quack...Quak...Honk...Honk…!”

A sound off so unique...humorous and funny...they actually forgot about eating (for the moment) and began taking turns in small groups.

Thus, a quacker barrel song of laughter was born called: The Sound of Quackers...and...like a tiny parade...they swam about in harmony until the cute creatures cavalry arrived.

:)

Eggster Monsalve
F.O.G. Tv Network Journalmist
